The paper discusses various algorithms and approaches for multi-view learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper covers topics such as co-training, multiple kernel learning, and subspace learning, which are commonly studied in the areas of computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the construction and evaluation of multiple views, which are relevant to the areas of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.IR.
